snippet.textDisplay:
This is my first time writing a comment for a video/song on Youtube. It has been 25 years since I have been Sajjad's fan: a 2 year old baby wriggling his butt to the song 'Babiya'. My mum had it tape recorded and I kept it playing and dancing till I started going to school. Then came an era of 'Chief Sahb' (I heard it way later than its release) 'Larri Adda' 'Cindrella' ...Sajjad always made me dance and smile and sing with him. This song of his is the second to make me cry after 'Is gham k siwa'...hats off yar!
That peace on his face when he pulls and pushes the surr...like its no effort at all. Zaw: good work girl, I love the english part more, nice accent!
Also, only if Zaw would have dragged her taan after English part a tiny bit more...it would have been perfect...but nonetheless, the girl is going places..sings awesome...Akhir beti kis ki hy :)
Rula dia yar again...my wife and lil daughter will never know why I cried lol...and even I don't know...the tears of listening to a heavenly composition.
snippet.textOriginal:

Also, only if Zaw would have dragged her taan after English part a tiny bit more...it would have been perfect...but nonetheless, the girl is going places..sings awesome...Akhir beti kis ki hy :)
